import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Get unique categories
genders = sample_info['Gender'].unique()
grades = sample_info['Grade'].unique()
stages = sample_info['Stage'].unique()

# Initialize the plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Position of bars on x-axis
bar_width = 0.35
bar_positions = np.arange(len(genders))

# Define bottom position for stacking
bottom_position = np.zeros(len(genders))

# Plotting each grade and stage as separate layers in the stack
for stage in stages:
    for grade in grades:
        count_data = []
        for gender in genders:
            count = sample_info[(sample_info['Gender'] == gender) & 
                                (sample_info['Grade'] == grade) & 
                                (sample_info['Stage'] == stage)].shape[0]
            count_data.append(count)
        
        plt.bar(bar_positions, count_data, bar_width, bottom=bottom_position, 
                label=f"Stage {stage}, Grade {grade}")
        bottom_position += np.array(count_data)

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Gender')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.title('Combined Distribution of Samples by Gender, Grade, and Stage')
plt.xticks(bar_positions, genders)
plt.legend(title='Stage and Grade', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Extract unique gene names from the cleaned probe features

import pandas as pd

def align_data(circRNA_data, methylation_data, probe_features):
    # Initialize lists to store ordered data
    ordered_circRNA_data = []
    ordered_methylation_data = []
    ordered_genes = []
    ordered_cpg_sites = []

    # Iterate over each gene in the probe features data
    for _, row in probe_features.iterrows():
        gene = row['gene']
        cpg_site = row['Unnamed: 0']

        # Extract circRNA expression for the current gene
        circRNA_gene_data = circRNA_data[circRNA_data['Gene'] == gene]
        
        # Extract methylation data for the current CpG site
        methylation_cpg_data = methylation_data[methylation_data['Unnamed: 0'] == cpg_site]

        if not circRNA_gene_data.empty and not methylation_cpg_data.empty:
            # Append the data to the ordered lists
            ordered_circRNA_data.append(circRNA_gene_data.iloc[0, 1:].values)  # Skipping 'CircRNA' column
            ordered_methylation_data.append(methylation_cpg_data.iloc[0, 1:].values)  # Skipping 'Unnamed: 0' column
            ordered_genes.append(gene)
            ordered_cpg_sites.append(cpg_site)

    # Convert lists to DataFrames
    ordered_circRNA_df = pd.DataFrame(ordered_circRNA_data, columns=circRNA_data.columns[1:], index=ordered_genes)
    ordered_methylation_df = pd.DataFrame(ordered_methylation_data, columns=methylation_data.columns[1:], index=ordered_cpg_sites)

    return ordered_circRNA_df, ordered_methylation_df

# Call the function with the filtered data
aligned_circRNA, aligned_methylation = align_data(circRNA_data_filtered_promoter, methylation_data_filtered, tss200_probe_features_filtered)

# Display the aligned data
print("Aligned circRNA data shape:", aligned_circRNA.shape)
print("Aligned methylation data shape:", aligned_methylation.shape)

from scipy.stats import spearmanr
import pandas as pd

# Initialize lists to store the results
genes = []
cpg_sites = []
correlations = []
p_values = []

# Iterate over each row (gene-CpG site pair)
for i in range(aligned_circRNA_common.shape[0]):
    gene = aligned_circRNA_common.index[i]
    cpg_site = aligned_methylation_common.index[i]
    
    # Extract circRNA expression and methylation levels
    circRNA_expression = aligned_circRNA_common.iloc[i, :].astype(float).values
    methylation_levels = aligned_methylation_common.iloc[i, :].astype(float).values
    
    # Calculate the Spearman correlation coefficient and p-value
    correlation, p_value = spearmanr(circRNA_expression, methylation_levels)
    
    # Store the results
    genes.append(gene)
    cpg_sites.append(cpg_site)
    correlations.append(correlation)
    p_values.append(p_value)

# Convert the results into a DataFrame
correlation_df = pd.DataFrame({'Gene': genes, 'CpG Site': cpg_sites, 'Correlation': correlations, 'P-value': p_values})

# Display the first few rows of the correlation results
print(correlation_df.head())
